(GRUNTS)

247
00:15:04.037 --> 00:15:05.037
Shit.

248
00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:06.905
(SIGHS)

249
00:15:17.050 --> 00:15:18.783
I have to go to Tony's.

250
00:15:18.851 --> 00:15:22.219
Hold on. Tony's? Now?

251
00:15:22.289 --> 00:15:24.838
He needs one of the tapes.
We're working together.

252
00:15:24.925 --> 00:15:26.391
Dinner's in a half hour.

253
00:15:26.459 --> 00:15:28.659
Make me a plate for later?

254
00:15:28.728 --> 00:15:31.168
Text me if you're gonna
be later than really late.

255
00:15:31.548 --> 00:15:33.588
I will. Bye.
Bye.

256
00:15:50.549 --> 00:15:52.316
(CHILDREN CHATTERING)

257
00:16:03.430 --> 00:16:04.430
(HORN HONKING)

258
00:16:18.211 --> 00:16:19.427
Hand me the screwdriver.

259
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:22.320
Okay.

260
00:16:26.685 --> 00:16:28.797
Hey. Tony.
Hey. Clay.

261
00:16:28.821 --> 00:16:31.155
Something wrong with her?
Nothing wrong yet.

262
00:16:31.223 --> 00:16:33.343
It's called taking
care of things.

263
00:16:34.293 --> 00:16:38.095
Dad. you remember Clay.
Yeah. sure.

264
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:39.580
How you doing. Clay?

265
00:16:39.666 --> 00:16:41.115
I'm well. thank you.

266
00:16:41.201 --> 00:16:42.900
So. Clay. what's up?

267
00:16:42.968 --> 00:16:44.735
Nothing. I was. uh...

268
00:16:44.804 --> 00:16:46.136
I was out for a ride.

269
00:16:46.206 --> 00:16:47.605
On the other side of town?

270
00:16:49.592 --> 00:16:51.470
That should do it.
Start her up.

271
00:16:51.494 --> 00:16:53.534
Hand me the rag.
I'll do it.

272
00:16:59.335 --> 00:17:01.552
If we got the timing right.
we'll hear it.

273
00:17:02.222 --> 00:17:03.521
Okay. flip the ignition.

274
00:17:05.058 --> 00:17:07.425
(ENGINE TURNING OVER)

275
00:17:07.494 --> 00:17:09.243
(ENGINE REVS)

276
00:17:11.831 --> 00:17:14.365
You hear that?
That's how it should sound.

277
00:17:14.434 --> 00:17:17.301
That sounds different?
Yeah. it's different.
Are you deaf?

278
00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:19.970
TONY: Sounds the same
as before.
Then you are deaf.

279
00:17:20.039 --> 00:17:22.756
That's so much smoother.
Night and day.
(TONY RESPONDS INDISTINCTLY)

280
00:17:22.826 --> 00:17:25.342
TONY'S DAD: I don't think so.
I know. and you should too.

281
00:17:25.412 --> 00:17:27.211
That's why I'm showing you this.

282
00:17:27.280 --> 00:17:28.329
Okay. shut her off.

283
00:17:29.832 --> 00:17:30.832
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

284
00:17:34.337 --> 00:17:35.770
I should get out of here.

285
00:17:35.838 --> 00:17:38.049
Sure you don't want
to stay for dinner?
No. thanks.

286
00:17:38.073 --> 00:17:39.440
My mom's making pork chops.

287
00:17:39.509 --> 00:17:42.376
If I'm not home soon. she'll
call the cops or something.

288
00:17:42.445 --> 00:17:44.144
They e-mailed
all the parents again.

289
00:17:44.213 --> 00:17:46.280
Oh. I know.
TONY'S DAD: She leave a note?

290
00:17:47.200 --> 00:17:48.515
Girl who killed herself?

291
00:17:49.919 --> 00:17:51.285
Uh...

292
00:17:51.354 --> 00:17:52.634
I don't know.

293
00:17:53.455 --> 00:17:54.922
(SPEAKS LOW IN SPANISH)

294
00:17:55.758 --> 00:17:57.391
Well. you listen to me.

295
00:17:57.460 --> 00:18:00.340
You ever do that to
your mother. I will kill you.
you understand?

296
00:18:01.197 --> 00:18:02.697
I'll kill you dead.

297
00:18:02.765 --> 00:18:03.765
Clean this shit up.

298
00:18:06.302 --> 00:18:08.636
No sense of irony
in that comment.

299
00:18:08.704 --> 00:18:10.137
None. He's. uh...

300
00:18:10.206 --> 00:18:11.238
He's a simple man.

301
00:18:11.307 --> 00:18:12.307
Yep.

302
00:18:13.176 --> 00:18:14.542
I'll see you later.

303
00:18:14.610 --> 00:18:16.690
Clay. I think you got
something that belongs
to me.

304
00:18:19.081 --> 00:18:20.161
I do?

305
00:18:22.135 --> 00:18:23.184
My keys.

306
00:18:23.886 --> 00:18:25.336
Oh. yeah. right. Here.

307
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:27.552
I'll see you later.

308
00:18:39.268 --> 00:18:41.602
HANNAH: <i>The rules here are
pretty simple.</i>

309
00:18:41.671 --> 00:18:42.770
<i>There are only two.</i>

310
00:18:43.806 --> 00:18:46.557
<i>Rule number one. you listen.</i>

311
00:18:46.626 --> 00:18:49.543
<i>Number two. you pass it on.</i>

312
00:18:49.612 --> 00:18:52.045
<i>Hopefully. neither one will
be easy.</i>

313
00:18:52.132 --> 00:18:55.299
<i>It's not supposed to be</i>
<i>easy. or I would have</i>
<i>e-mailed you an MP3.</i>

314
00:18:55.368 --> 00:18:58.102
<i>When you're done listening
to all 13 sides.</i>

315
00:18:58.171 --> 00:19:01.539
<i>because there are 13 sides
to every story...</i>

316
00:19:01.608 --> 00:19:03.624
<i>Rewind the tapes.
put them back in the box.</i>

317
00:19:03.693 --> 00:19:05.726
<i>and pass them on
to the next person.</i>

318
00:19:05.794 --> 00:19:07.528
Why the hell am I on this?

319
00:19:07.597 --> 00:19:11.565
<i>Oh. and the box of tapes
should have included a map.</i>

320
00:19:11.634 --> 00:19:15.085
<i>I'll be mentioning several
spots around our beloved city.</i>

321
00:19:15.154 --> 00:19:16.798
<i>I can't force you to visit them.</i>

322
00:19:16.822 --> 00:19:21.825
<i>but if you'd like a little</i>
<i>more insight. head for</i>
<i>the stars.</i>

323
00:19:21.894 --> 00:19:25.296
<i>Or. you know. just throw</i>
<i>the map away and I'll</i>
<i>never know...</i>

324
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:27.698
<i>Or will I?</i>

325
00:19:30.536 --> 00:19:33.337
<i>You see. in case you're
tempted to break the rules.</i>

326
00:19:33.406 --> 00:19:36.323
<i>understand I did make a copy
of these tapes.</i>

327
00:19:36.392 --> 00:19:38.425
<i>and I left them
with a trusted individual</i>

328
00:19:38.494 --> 00:19:41.495
<i>who. if this package doesn't
make it through all of you.</i>

329
00:19:41.563 --> 00:19:44.815
<i>will release those copies
in a very public manner.</i>

330
00:19:44.884 --> 00:19:47.251
This was not
a spur-of-the-moment decision.

331
00:19:47.319 --> 00:19:49.620
<i>Do not take me for granted.</i>

332
00:19:49.689 --> 00:19:50.755
<i>Not again.</i>

333
00:19:50.823 --> 00:19:51.823
I never did!

334
00:19:53.292 --> 00:19:55.120
(CAR HORN HONKING)
Whoa!

335
00:19:55.144 --> 00:19:57.011
(HONKING)
(TIRES SQUEAL)

336
00:19:58.715 --> 00:19:59.847
(TAPE PLAYER CLATTERS)

337
00:20:01.066 --> 00:20:03.117
(TIRES SQUEALING AWAY)

338
00:20:04.653 --> 00:20:06.053
(GRUNTS)

339
00:20:07.489 --> 00:20:08.755
(COUGHS)

340
00:20:13.229 --> 00:20:14.728
(PANTING)

341
00:20:18.901 --> 00:20:19.901
(GROANS SOFTLY)

342
00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:23.170
Oh. shit.

343
00:20:37.002 --> 00:20:38.122
(GRUNTS)

344
00:20:58.174 --> 00:21:00.007
HANNAH:<i> Do what I say.</i>

345
00:21:00.076 --> 00:21:01.775
<i>Not more. not less.</i>

346
00:21:04.547 --> 00:21:05.746
<i>You're being watched.</i>

347
00:21:20.196 --> 00:21:21.228
Everything okay?

348
00:21:21.297 --> 00:21:22.807
Yeah. No. I just
forgot something.

349
00:21:22.831 --> 00:21:24.131
Clay. your forehead!

350
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.466
What? It's nothing.

351
00:21:25.535 --> 00:21:27.168
Did you fall off your bike?

352
00:21:27.236 --> 00:21:29.915
Low-hanging branch. I went
through the woods.
It was dark.

353
00:21:29.939 --> 00:21:31.172
I'll get the first aid kit.

354
00:21:31.240 --> 00:21:33.074
I don't need first aid.

355
00:21:33.142 --> 00:21:35.176
You are bleeding.
You need ointment.

356
00:21:35.244 --> 00:21:37.404
Mom. please don't say
"ointment."

357
00:21:39.982 --> 00:21:41.299
I'm fine. really.

358
00:21:41.367 --> 00:21:44.012
What happened?
I told you. bike.
branch. skin.

359
00:21:44.036 --> 00:21:45.152
That's all?

360
00:21:45.221 --> 00:21:46.965
Mom. I tell you everything
about my life

361
00:21:46.989 --> 00:21:49.039
because it is so fascinating.
I promise.

362
00:21:49.108 --> 00:21:51.253
I'll clean it up.
I have to go.
Tony's waiting.

363
00:21:51.277 --> 00:21:52.277
Ah-ah.

364
00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:57.014
Your helmet. please.

365
00:22:12.681 --> 00:22:14.014
HANNAH: Love the helmet.

366
00:22:15.251 --> 00:22:16.934
It's adorable.

367
00:22:17.003 --> 00:22:20.437
You mean "adorable" in a
helpless baby animal sort of
way. I'm guessing.

368
00:22:20.506 --> 00:22:22.317
Aren't you afraid
of helmet hair?

369
00:22:22.341 --> 00:22:24.975
My hair does the same thing
no matter what.
just sits there.

370
00:22:26.045 --> 00:22:27.527
You just need some product.

371
00:22:27.597 --> 00:22:29.942
A little effort to style it.
blow-dry it in the morning.

372
00:22:29.966 --> 00:22:31.949
And sacrifice my masculinity?

373
00:22:32.018 --> 00:22:34.378
That ship has sailed.
don't you think?

374
00:22:35.388 --> 00:22:38.455
Forgive me for wanting to keep
my brains in my head.

375
00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:41.157
Instead of. say. some other
regions. like most boys?

376
00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:44.762
Come on. Helmet.
you've got bathrooms to clean.

377
00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:48.331
You mean "we've got."
Mmm. I don't. actually.

378
00:22:48.401 --> 00:22:51.167
Oh. uh. party at my house
tomorrow night.

379
00:22:51.236 --> 00:22:54.436
You're invited.
It's mandatory.
Don't bring the helmet.

380
00:22:57.309 --> 00:23:00.176
Cool. Where. uh...
Where do you live?

381
00:23:00.245 --> 00:23:04.331
HANNAH:<i> Put your finger</i>
<i>n "C." your other</i>
<i>finger on "4."</i>

382
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:07.734
<i>Bring them together.
That's our first red star.</i>

383
00:23:08.504 --> 00:23:09.570
<i>I know. right?</i>

384
00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:12.772
<i>A map. Old school. again.</i>

385
00:23:12.841 --> 00:23:14.174
<i>No Google Maps.</i>

386
00:23:14.242 --> 00:23:16.360
<i>no app. no chance
for the interwebs</i>

387
00:23:16.429 --> 00:23:18.696
<i>to make everything worse.
like it does.</i>

388
00:23:33.146 --> 00:23:34.728
(ENGINE REVS)

389
00:24:03.442 --> 00:24:05.142
(ENGINE REVS. TIRES SQUEAL)

390
00:24:13.586 --> 00:24:16.737
HANNAH:<i> You've arrived</i>
<i>at my first house in</i>
<i>this shitty town...</i>

391
00:24:18.240 --> 00:24:20.941
<i>Where I threw my first
and only party...</i>

392
00:24:22.544 --> 00:24:25.112
<i>And where I met Justin Foley...</i>

393
00:24:25.181 --> 00:24:27.014
<i>The subject of our first tape.</i>

394
00:24:27.083 --> 00:24:29.416
(ROCK MUSIC
PLAYS INDISTINCTLY)

395
00:24:31.420 --> 00:24:33.687
<i>It was just a party.</i>

396
00:24:33.756 --> 00:24:36.656
<i>I didn't know it was
the beginning of the end.</i>

397
00:24:36.726 --> 00:24:39.159
(MUSIC CONTINUES)
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

398
00:24:42.364 --> 00:24:46.666
<i>Justin. you were in love</i>
<i>with my friend Kat.</i>
<i>My only friend.</i>

399
00:24:46.736 --> 00:24:48.736
He came! Clay's here!

400
00:24:48.804 --> 00:24:51.238
(CHUCKLES)
I win! You owe
me five dollars.

401
00:24:51.306 --> 00:24:52.372
Oh. my God.

402
00:24:52.441 --> 00:24:54.319
You bet on me?
Against you.

403
00:24:54.343 --> 00:24:59.412
Last party I saw Clay at...
Mmm. my birthday.
fourth grade.

404
00:24:59.481 --> 00:25:01.615
I still remember that clown.
Mmm!

405
00:25:01.683 --> 00:25:03.550
Oh. my God.
He was a heroin addict.

406
00:25:03.619 --> 00:25:07.755
My mother. the social worker.
hired a recovering
heroin addict.

407
00:25:07.823 --> 00:25:09.589
He had the shakes.

408
00:25:09.658 --> 00:25:13.127
Okay. uh. drinks. Come on.
Excuse me.

409
00:25:13.195 --> 00:25:15.428
I just thought he was nervous.
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

410
00:25:15.497 --> 00:25:16.857
Hey.
Hi. Kat.

411
00:25:17.833 --> 00:25:20.345
This is quite a turnout.
People are happy
to see you go.

412
00:25:20.369 --> 00:25:23.603
I really just threw it
so Hannah could finally
meet some people

413
00:25:23.672 --> 00:25:25.906
before I depart this realm.

414
00:25:25.975 --> 00:25:27.307
I met Helmet.

415
00:25:27.376 --> 00:25:29.287
Clay doesn't count.
You met him at work.

416
00:25:29.311 --> 00:25:32.112
I feel like that should count.
Of course you do.

417
00:25:32.181 --> 00:25:35.548
Okay. refills. Clay. what is
your drink?

418
00:25:35.617 --> 00:25:36.784
Uh. Sprite.

419
00:25:36.852 --> 00:25:38.764
Oh. my God. you are priceless.

420
00:25:38.788 --> 00:25:41.148
You are a gem.
You'll have a beer.

421
00:25:42.057 --> 00:25:43.490
Sure. I like beer.

422
00:25:43.558 --> 00:25:45.358
TYLER: Kat.
Oh. Picture.

423
00:25:46.695 --> 00:25:47.795
(SHUTTER CLICKS)

424
00:25:51.066 --> 00:25:53.801
Stop having so much fun. Clay.

425
00:25:53.869 --> 00:25:55.435
I'm having fun. totally.

426
00:25:55.971 --> 00:25:56.971
Woot!

427
00:25:59.508 --> 00:26:00.808
You're too buttoned up.

428
00:26:03.712 --> 00:26:05.011
(LAUGHING)

429
00:26:07.432 --> 00:26:08.712
Hey there.

430
00:26:09.034 --> 00:26:10.333
Hey.

431
00:26:10.402 --> 00:26:13.770
You're. um. you're the new girl.

432
00:26:14.372 --> 00:26:15.639
Apparently.

433
00:26:15.708 --> 00:26:17.808
Uh. I like your laugh.

434
00:26:17.876 --> 00:26:18.976
Thanks.

435
00:26:19.044 --> 00:26:21.979
I like your understated
sense of fashion.

436
00:26:22.047 --> 00:26:23.947
(CHUCKLES) Thanks.

437
00:26:24.016 --> 00:26:25.682
KAT: Bryce.

438
00:26:25.751 --> 00:26:28.831
Better go hit the keg
and catch up.
You're an hour behind.

439
00:26:30.489 --> 00:26:32.266
I'll see you later...
I hope.

440
00:26:32.290 --> 00:26:33.389
See you.

441
00:26:35.494 --> 00:26:38.795
Oh. God. no.
Solid no. Hannah.

442
00:26:38.864 --> 00:26:41.064
He is. like. frat boy
Darth Vader.

443
00:26:41.133 --> 00:26:42.432
He didn't seem that bad.

444
00:26:43.201 --> 00:26:44.245
I was being kind.

445
00:26:44.269 --> 00:26:45.502
She kind of was.

446
00:26:48.406 --> 00:26:49.640
I think I want a beer too.

447
00:26:51.076 --> 00:26:53.076
Okay. then. Princess Leia.

448
00:26:54.312 --> 00:26:55.946
Oh. my God. you're both nerds.

449
00:26:56.448 --> 00:26:57.648
Have fun.

450
00:27:02.955 --> 00:27:04.075
Are you gonna tell her?

451
00:27:05.224 --> 00:27:06.389
Tell her what?

452
00:27:06.458 --> 00:27:09.226
Oh. please. I've known you
this entire century.

453
00:27:10.295 --> 00:27:11.929
Well. give me a break.

454
00:27:11.998 --> 00:27:13.631
I'm not good with the...

455
00:27:13.699 --> 00:27:16.700
You know. and the gay rumors
only recently subsided.

456
00:27:16.769 --> 00:27:19.169
Mmm. So the stakes are
high for you.

457
00:27:21.007 --> 00:27:23.440
It's like. around her.
I can be different. you know?

458
00:27:23.509 --> 00:27:25.375
I'm the new and improved
Clay Jensen.

459
00:27:25.444 --> 00:27:28.846
High school sophomore.
archaeologist
slash-adventurer.

460
00:27:30.249 --> 00:27:34.118
Clay. sweets. you're a prize.

461
00:27:34.186 --> 00:27:39.489
But from my limited
observation. she has
terrible taste in guys.

462
00:27:41.861 --> 00:27:44.261
You won't say anything to her?

463
00:27:45.731 --> 00:27:47.011
Only if it comes up.

464
00:27:47.199 --> 00:27:48.365
Kat!

465
00:27:49.168 --> 00:27:50.467
(CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

466
00:27:58.860 --> 00:27:59.893
(PHONE CLICKS)

467
00:28:12.491 --> 00:28:14.291
Shit!
Watch it!

468
00:28:15.945 --> 00:28:20.113
(LAUGHING. YELLING)

469
00:28:20.182 --> 00:28:21.815
No...

470
00:28:21.883 --> 00:28:22.982
KAT: Meet the boys.

471
00:28:23.069 --> 00:28:27.337
Justin Foley is mine.
and Zach Dempsey for you.

472
00:28:27.406 --> 00:28:29.439
Zach Dempsey? Really?

473
00:28:29.508 --> 00:28:31.174
What? Zach's sweet?

474
00:28:32.244 --> 00:28:33.543
I can't see!

475
00:28:33.612 --> 00:28:35.345
Not the mane!

476
00:28:35.414 --> 00:28:37.848
Okay. yeah. he's kind of dumb.

477
00:28:37.917 --> 00:28:40.851
but he's the sweet kind
of dumb. which is the
best kind.

478
00:28:44.189 --> 00:28:45.455
Yes.

479
00:28:45.523 --> 00:28:48.842
Liberty High's star athletes.
ladies and gentlemen.

480
00:28:48.928 --> 00:28:50.727
So impressive.

481
00:28:50.796 --> 00:28:53.680
Sorry. boys. Can't have you
in Hannah's house soaking wet.

482
00:28:53.766 --> 00:28:55.198
Seriously?

483
00:28:55.267 --> 00:28:57.267
Oh. my God. look at yourselves.

484
00:28:58.420 --> 00:28:59.703
Better?

485
00:28:59.771 --> 00:29:03.557
Improvement. for sure.
but sorry. it's still a no-go.

486
00:29:03.625 --> 00:29:05.137
Come on! It's not a party
without us.

487
00:29:05.161 --> 00:29:06.361
KAT: We'll take our chances.

488
00:29:06.412 --> 00:29:07.711
Go dry off.

489
00:29:07.780 --> 00:29:09.846
Your loss. milady.

490
00:29:09.915 --> 00:29:11.981
Idiots. I can't even...

491
00:29:12.050 --> 00:29:13.283
